text: Chishma () is a rural locality (a selo) in Ismailovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 472 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 22 km from Dyurtyuli. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Chishma, Dyurtyulinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
